335
00:24:05,725 --> 00:24:08,078
Where is that punk now?

336
00:24:12,866 --> 00:24:14,984
Kang Yeong Jin!

337
00:24:26,196 --> 00:24:28,106
Did you meet with Ha Won?

338
00:24:29,716 --> 00:24:33,512
How was your father-daughter reunion after so long?

339
00:24:33,954 --> 00:24:38,684
Do you really think that Ha Won is my daughter?

340
00:24:39,977 --> 00:24:42,354
Why do you keep wasting your time with such nonsense?

341
00:24:42,771 --> 00:24:43,647
What?

342
00:24:43,981 --> 00:24:47,342
There was nothing going on between me and Ok Seon!

343
00:24:47,342 --> 00:24:48,443
Don't you dare lie to me!

344
00:24:48,527 --> 00:24:54,449
You two fell head over heels for one another while I was away working!

345
00:24:54,950 --> 00:24:57,144
The only thing that the either of us were good at was exercising

346
00:24:57,144 --> 00:24:59,621
which is why we opened a taekwondo center together! That's it!

347
00:24:59,646 --> 00:25:03,317
Why did Ha Won's mother die at your apartment, then?

348
00:25:03,317 --> 00:25:06,195
She was at my house because of an issue related to the center, and--

349
00:25:06,195 --> 00:25:09,156
You two were trying to run away together, but Ha Won's mom died

350
00:25:09,156 --> 00:25:10,882
so you ran away by yourself. Isn't that what happened?

351
00:25:10,882 --> 00:25:16,597
Geez. You know better than I do that Ok Seon wasn't that kind of person!

352
00:25:16,647 --> 00:25:21,793
I know all about the fact that you put the center up for sale, too.

353
00:25:24,463 --> 00:25:28,400
Yes. I sold it without telling Ok Seon.

354
00:25:30,027 --> 00:25:32,988
I was being chased by debt collectors, and I went a bit crazy for a second

355
00:25:32,988 --> 00:25:35,324
which is why I sold the center!

356
00:25:35,324 --> 00:25:38,327
Ok Seon found out about that, and came to see me.

357
00:25:38,327 --> 00:25:40,579
And then... she died.

358
00:25:41,830 --> 00:25:42,831
What... did you say?

359
00:25:42,831 --> 00:25:44,958
I really do deserve to die.

360
00:25:45,918 --> 00:25:50,464
But I feel even worse toward Ok Seon, who died because of that.

361
00:25:53,467 --> 00:25:58,012
I came home to run away from the debt collectors.

362
00:25:58,012 --> 00:26:00,541
But the house was already in flames when I arrived.

363
00:26:00,541 --> 00:26:05,020
Ok Seon was trying to rescue the woman, next door, and didn't get out in time.

364
00:26:05,437 --> 00:26:08,741
Apparently, the ring that Ok Seon was holding was from the woman next door

365
00:26:08,741 --> 00:26:10,943
Who asked it be given to her own son, but...

366
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:15,364
Are you going to continue to doubt that poor woman

367
00:26:15,739 --> 00:26:18,925
who died while trying to save someone else's life?

368
00:26:18,951 --> 00:26:24,456
I didn't even know that, and hated Ok Seon.

369
00:26:26,066 --> 00:26:28,943
And I even hated poor Ha Won...

370
00:26:30,045 --> 00:26:35,260
who treasured that ring as her mother's keepsake!

371
00:27:09,818 --> 00:27:14,506
What's the matter, child? Do you have a sore throat?

372
00:27:14,506 --> 00:27:17,442
Oh, it's nothing like that.

373
00:27:25,091 --> 00:27:26,559
Meet me in the storage room!

374
00:27:39,064 --> 00:27:43,543
Why did you get here so late? Didn't you hear my cue?

375
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:45,687
You call that noise a proper cue?

376
00:27:45,687 --> 00:27:48,498
Yeah! That means, "see me now!"

377
00:27:49,566 --> 00:27:51,243
Just text me.

378
00:27:51,243 --> 00:27:53,253
That's no fun at all!

379
00:27:53,637 --> 00:27:55,972
Look at the mess we're in because of my grandfather.

380
00:27:55,972 --> 00:27:58,600
We have to hide away like this.

381
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:01,010
Why do you hate your grandfather so much?

382
00:28:06,625 --> 00:28:08,793
You know...

383
00:28:10,921 --> 00:28:13,231
my mom was a really ordinary woman.

384
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:18,195
Ordinary enough to make someone wonder how she even met someone like my dad.

385
00:28:20,639 --> 00:28:23,567
Seeing as how she never talked about my dad to me...

386
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:26,478
it's clear that they didn't part on good terms.

387
00:28:30,832 --> 00:28:33,168
I came to Haneul House because I had a lot of questions.

388
00:28:35,087 --> 00:28:37,381
That's more of a reason to not hide away in a place like this

389
00:28:37,381 --> 00:28:38,882
and ask the Chairman your questions.

390
00:28:38,966 --> 00:28:40,550
Isn't that right?

391
00:28:43,428 --> 00:28:45,722
I saw a trace of my father for the first time, here.

392
00:28:51,170 --> 00:28:53,071
My dad's name is carved into this.

393
00:28:55,232 --> 00:28:57,717
I think he used this, a long time ago.

394
00:29:00,028 --> 00:29:01,971
But only the camera is here.

395
00:29:01,971 --> 00:29:03,782
There aren't any photos.

396
00:29:05,867 --> 00:29:07,969
All right, then. Let's report this to him.

397
00:29:07,978 --> 00:29:08,996
Huh?

398
00:29:09,371 --> 00:29:12,891
Let's report to your dad that we like each other!

399
00:29:12,891 --> 00:29:16,853
All right. Reporting time!

400
00:29:18,355 --> 00:29:19,764
There we go.

401
00:29:22,050 --> 00:29:23,802
Dad

402
00:29:25,262 --> 00:29:27,139
Dad?

403
00:29:45,916 --> 00:29:47,175
There we go.

404
00:29:49,061 --> 00:29:52,230
It's a mess in there, isn't it? And it smells like gas, too, doesn't it?

405
00:29:52,247 --> 00:29:55,458
I like that, since that's what you smell like.

406
00:29:57,236 --> 00:30:01,965
You seemed so cool, driving around in a huge truck like this one.

407
00:30:04,326 --> 00:30:05,928
I'm sorry.

408
00:30:07,054 --> 00:30:09,932
I misunderstood something greatly this whole time.

409
00:30:12,434 --> 00:30:14,436
I trusted Mom.

410
00:30:15,729 --> 00:30:19,174
Yes, you were a better person than I was.

411
00:30:19,174 --> 00:30:22,619
I should've trusted your mom, too.

412
00:30:22,619 --> 00:30:25,797
You trusted Mom too, Dad.

413
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:34,164
I thought about why you never got us tested, kept on searching for Mr. Young Jin

414
00:30:35,457 --> 00:30:40,629
even when you said that I wasn't really your daughter.

415
00:30:43,757 --> 00:30:47,210
You felt bad that you couldn't be by Mom's side back then

416
00:30:47,219 --> 00:30:51,123
when she was going through all that.

417
00:30:51,123 --> 00:30:53,308
Isn't that right?

418
00:30:54,393 --> 00:31:00,782
And so you wanted to find Mr. Young Jin and ask for forgiveness, right?

419
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:05,129
I'm sorry.

420
00:31:05,862 --> 00:31:10,408
To both you... and your mother.

421
00:31:11,326 --> 00:31:14,621
Your mother... she...

422
00:31:18,458 --> 00:31:20,794
Don't be sorry, Dad.

423
00:31:22,921 --> 00:31:24,506
Let's go back home now, Dad.

424
00:31:27,050 --> 00:31:32,297
I didn't know how much your stepmother and Yoo Na had been harassing you.

425
00:31:32,306 --> 00:31:37,519
It'll be hard for you if you come back home now.

426
00:31:39,947 --> 00:31:42,424
But she's someone I chose. I can't cast her aside now.

427
00:31:42,424 --> 00:31:44,442
You understand what I'm saying, right?

428
00:31:46,553 --> 00:31:51,950
So... give me some time.

429
00:31:52,534 --> 00:31:59,082
I'll make it so that our family can be a real family.

430
00:32:00,417 --> 00:32:03,878
I still have some work left to do, too.

431
00:32:06,006 --> 00:32:09,176
Oh! You're home, Honey?

432
00:32:10,761 --> 00:32:13,596
Honey. Did you meet Kang Yeong Jin?

433
00:32:13,596 --> 00:32:16,433
Well, um...

434
00:32:16,433 --> 00:32:18,736
Did you meet him, or not?

435
00:32:18,736 --> 00:32:20,954
I... did meet with him.

436
00:32:20,954 --> 00:32:24,583
It seemed like you were trying to find Ha Won's real father

437
00:32:24,583 --> 00:32:27,169
so it'd be good for everyone if we did that for her, right?

438
00:32:27,169 --> 00:32:30,255
I was just trying to get money from him, as compensation for raising her--

439
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:31,598
Park Soo Gyeong!

440
00:32:31,598 --> 00:32:33,867
Y-yes?

441
00:32:33,867 --> 00:32:36,987
Ha Won isn't that man's daughter.

442
00:32:36,995 --> 00:32:38,863
She's my daughter!

443
00:32:42,568 --> 00:32:45,170
Honey. And you, Yoo Na!

444
00:32:45,254 --> 00:32:46,738
Yes, Dad?

445
00:32:46,738 --> 00:32:50,008
How have you been treating Ha Won all this time?

446
00:32:51,493 --> 00:32:53,453
Tell me, right now!

